JOHANNESBURG - Hugh Masekela's fans will celebrate his life at two memorial services in Johannesburg on Friday.
	
	The jazz legend and anti-apartheid activist died after a long battle with prostate cancer on Tuesday. Mourners will gather at the Hugh Masekela Heritage Park at Zoo Lake for day-long services. READ: Sal Masekela pays tribute to his father, 'Bra Hugh' The Heritage Park chronicles Masekela's six-decade career as an artist and activist. Visuals, footage and audio that reflect his life journey will be broadcast. A second service will take place in Alexandra while the main memorial service will be held on Sunday in Soweto. His funeral will be private, as per his family's request. eNCA